SIMPLE: glaver
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Glaver
<hw>Glav"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[Of Celtic origin;
cf. W. <ets>glafr</ets> flattery.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To prate; to
jabber; to babble.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Here many, clepid filosophirs, <qex>glavern</qex> diversely.</q>
<rj><qau>Wyclif.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To flatter; to wheedle.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Some slavish, <qex>glavering</qex>, flattering parasite.</q>
<rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Glaverer</ent>⟦br⟧
